,Recommended,298520,16046540,"Posted: 28 May, 2015",all,Hitaro,"Orbital Gear is a fun fast paced shooter with some really fun design choices.Pros:[+] Guns are satisfying. There are 12 in all, and each one is very unique. Using a different gun feels like using a different class in Tf2, and each one has a satisfying hit. There are a lot of high impact weapons, so dieing is quick, but so are respawn timers so there's very little to no downtime.[+] Movement is great. It takes a little bit to get used to the gravity mechanic, but once you understand how to manipulate it in your favor, sling shotting yourself across the map feels really great. There are single player time trials to help you learn them.[+] High skill high reward. The nice thing about the game is that it's consistent. There's a lot of room to learn the movement system, a lot of room to learn how to position yourself relative to certain guns, aiming with projectiles has a ton of depth, and overall just being good at aiming + Reaction is very rewarding. Some combinations will seem overpowered, but then you realize that there are counters to most everything and most things are pretty balanced. For example, when I first got the game it seemed to me the gauntlet was the most broken weapon in the game, but after a couple hours you realize that it gets absolutely destroyed by any of the shotgun-esque weapons and overall just positioning.Cons:[-] Very little lag compensation. Servers are player hosted, and even when playing with people who have relatively low ping, (like 20-50) you'll have people teleporting their locations. Super frustrating and honestly the biggest negative.[-] Lack of feedback. There's  no indication of whether or not you hit somebody else. You can shoot at someone multiple times and have no idea if you've actually damaged them. Not usually an issue since most weapons tend to be very high damaging, and most of the time 1-4 shots will kill someone (lending to the fast paced nature of the game, but would be a nice, easy fix.[-] Small Player base. I've checked other server regions a couple times, and asian /australian regions have no servers usually. American and European servers tend to have a couple servers running so if you live in either of those places it should be fine.Verdict: As of writing this the game is on sale for a dollar, and at that price the game is absolutely worth getting. I see it's also been in packs and bundles before for a couple dollars and that'd also be worth it. I personally wouldn't recommend the game for 10 dollars, but just a little bit off of that and its an amazing deal."
