76561197972390763,Recommended,298520,16110315,"Posted: 31 May, 2015",all,Exige,"Plays like an arena shooter (like Unreal Tournament or Quake), but in 2D and with interesting movement mechanics due to the gravity. Fast-paced fun. Highly recommended.However: there is basically nobody playing on the public servers... so if you buy this game, get the 4-pack and give copies to your friends. Otherwise you'll have nobody to play with. Since there is no single player mode and no bots, having opponents is a requirement.The game has two modes: a free-for-all deathmatch mode and a team mode based around capturing objectives. The deathmatch mode is fun and works well but the team mode feels incomplete. For example, there is no direct feedback when you hit a target with your weapon. It's also nearly impossible to find enough players to organize teams... so practically speaking, you'll only ever play the deathmatch mode with your own friends."
