,Recommended,298520,34585564,Posted: 29 August,all,ＲＡＧＥｘＴＲＯＬＬ,"Nice graphics, solid gameplay, cool gravitational mechanics, and different weapons to suit different playstyles. This is a good game missing a playerbase. You might find one or two servers sporadically at any given time throughout the day but don't expect much more than that until one of the steam sales.There are two multiplayer modes: Deathmatch and Team Deathmatch which I'm not going to bother explaining. What I will make note of however is that in multiplayer, all players are given access to all weapons in the game, which you can switch out in between lives if you'd like which makes for a level playing field with the only deciding factor in matches being player skill.There is also a very loose single player mode which is basically a time trial consisting of clearing a level of enemies as quickly as possible for up to 3 points (3 if you're quick, 2 is you're so-so, 1 if you're slow.) You start with the default weapon and progress through a set of different levels with progressively harder enemies. Once you've  accumulated enough points in a set you open up another weapon class and repeat. Though again this is meant more for getting a player accustomed to the mechanics of the game and becoming familar with the weapons, so it lacks the intensity and enjoyment that PVP matches have.All and all I recommend this game, but not for $10 given it's lack of a playerbase despite the games heavy reliance on needing one to keep it's replayability since it's a PVP game first and forermost. I bought the 4 pack of this game during one of the steam sales for 90% off and felt it was a bargin, even if the game is dead 85% of the time. So pick up the 4 pack when it's 90% off and give it a go with some friends.Also, if anyone on my friends list ends up reading this. I've had 3 copies of this game sitting in my inventory for the past two years waiting to be given out god damnit."
